  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "I find it difficult to catch up on and refer to earlier conversations on Desktop due to a poor scrolling experience. Here are the main pain points:\n\n1) Scrolling with mouse wheel is way too sensitive. It just flies off the handle.\n2) I can't scroll with page up and down (nor ctrl-f to search like in most web-based chats, but that's a separate issue)\n3) If I try to use my mouse to scroll, the bar disappears or it is too tiny.\n\nSimplest fix would probably be to bind PgUp/Down to scrolling a page (good bounty!). Alternatively decrease sensitivity, if this is a setting somewhere.\n\ncc @hesterbruikman @vkjr",
